    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by sustained global mobility, surveillance, and deterrence operations amid escalating regional tensions. The Western Pacific remains a critical focus, with RIMPAC 2026 exercises ongoing and a clear strategic reorientation of Coast Guard assets from the Middle East to counter Chinese maritime expansion. The Middle East remains volatile, with recent Iranian attacks on Gulf states and U.S. bases in Jordan triggering retaliatory strikes, marking a dangerous escalation in the ongoing conflict. The U.S. Navy&#39;s amphibious readiness is active, as evidenced by the return of USS Fort Lauderdale from a prolonged Caribbean deployment, reflecting sustained amphibious capabilities. High-altitude ISR and tanker aircraft operations over North America and the Pacific underscore the need for long-range strike and surveillance support, while strategic airlift platforms like the C-5M Galaxy and C-130 Hercules indicate ongoing global logistics and humanitarian missions. The expansion of stealthy cruise and anti-ship missile procurement further signals a strategic emphasis on enhancing long-range strike capabilities to counter adversarial A2/AD strategies. Overall, the military landscape reflects a dynamic and adaptive strategy to address global threats, with a clear emphasis on Indo-Pacific deterrence and Middle Eastern crisis management, but with heightened risks of further escalation in the Gulf region.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
